        <heading>SECTION A103—DEFINITIONS—AMENDED.</heading>
        <para>
          <num>(a)</num>
          <text>HIGH RISK BUILDING: Any building (except essential and hazardous facilities listed in Section A102.2) having an occupant load of 100 or more, as determined by 2016 CBC Section 1004.</text>
        </para>
        <para>
          <num>(b)</num>
          <text>LOW RISK BUILDING: Any building (except essential and hazardous facilities listed in Section A102.2) having an occupant load of less than 100 occupants as determined by 2016 CBC Section 1004. (Ord. 2016-10 § 5; Ord. 2013-13 § 4; Ord. 2010-16 § 4; Ord. 2007-11 § 4; Ord. 1999-8 § 5)</text>
