        <section>
          <num>27.28.048</num>
          <heading>MAXIMUM COVERAGE OF PARCELS.</heading>
          <text>There is no maximum coverage of parcels in this district. (Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.050</num>
          <heading>MAXIMUM FLOOR AREA RATIO.</heading>
          <text>The maximum floor area ratio in this district is 3.0. (Ord. 1992-15 § 19, 1992; Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.052</num>
          <heading>YARD AREAS GENERALLY.</heading>
          <para>
            <num>(a)</num>
            <text>Buildings shall not be constructed or enlarged unless the required yard areas are provided and maintained in connection with such building, structure or enlargement. Yards required by this chapter may be combined in various ways through a planned unit development to preserve and enhance the existing site elements (including sunlight, protection of existing heritage trees, creeks, waterways, historical or architecturally important sites, or structures, and archaeological sites). Yard combinations shall be considered by the City as part of the planning application review.</text>
          </para>
          <para>
            <num>(b)</num>
            <text>For one family and two family dwellings the regulations of the R1-B district shall apply. (Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
          </para>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.053</num>
          <heading>BUILDING HEIGHT AND SPECIAL YARD REQUIREMENTS—DOWNTOWN SPECIFIC PLAN GATEWAY AREA.</heading>
          <para>
            <num>(1)</num>
            <text>Properties within the Gateway area as defined in the Downtown Specific Plan shall conform with the following building height and yard requirements: interior side yard and rear yard setbacks shall conform with sections 27.28.056 and 27.22.058:</text>
          </para>
          <text>
            <table>
              <tr>
                <th>Property Street Frontage</th>
                <th>Yard Requirement</th>
                <th>Building Height Standard</th>
                <th>Additional Yard Requirement</th>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Third and Fourth Avenues</td>
                <td>Buildings shall be set back a minimum of 15 feet to a maximum of 20 feet from the Third and Fourth Avenue property lines for at least 60% of the building frontage.</td>
                <td>Building height at the setback line shall be a minimum of 20 feet to a maximum of 30 feet.</td>
                <td>Portions of the building over 30 feet in height shall be setback a minimum of 8 feet behind the front building facade as established in conformance with the "yard requirement" column.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Other Gateway Streets</td>
                <td>Buildings shall be set back a minimum of 15 feet to a maximum of 20 feet from the street property line for at least 60% of the building frontage.</td>
                <td>Building height at the setback line shall be a maximum of 25 feet.</td>
                <td>Portions of the building over 25 feet in height shall be setback a minimum of 8 feet behind the front building facade as established in conformance with the "yard requirement" column.</td>
              </tr>
            </table>
          </text>
          <text>(Ord. 1994-28 § 3, 1994).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.054</num>
          <heading>CONFORMANCE WITH GATEWAY DESIGN STANDARDS.</heading>
          <text>All building additions and new buildings within the Gateway area as defined in the Downtown Specific Plan shall conform with the Gateway Design Guidelines. (Ord. 1994-28 § 3, 1994).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.056</num>
          <heading>SIDE YARDS.</heading>
          <text>Side yards of not less than fifteen (15) feet shall be provided and maintained. (Ord. 1992-2 § 9, 1992; Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.058</num>
          <heading>REAR YARDS.</heading>
          <text>Rear yards of not less than twenty-five (25) feet shall be provided and maintained. (Ord. 1992-2 § 10, 1992; Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.060</num>
          <heading>LANDSCAPING.</heading>
          <text>At least twenty (20) percent of the required rear yard shall be landscaped and planted as defined in Section 27.04.267 for usable open space only (exclusive of parking areas, driveways, or accessory facilities) and maintained in common. (Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.062</num>
          <heading>USABLE OPEN SPACE REQUIREMENTS.</heading>
          <para>
            <num>(a)</num>
            <text>The open space requirements of this district are in addition to open space requirements resulting from the approval and filing of a subdivision map, or open space as imposed on a planned development in accord with the City's general plan or any required off-street parking areas or driveways. Open space required by this section is intended to be for the use and enjoyment of the residents of the development.</text>
          </para>
          <para>
            <num>(b)</num>
            <text>Each dwelling unit shall be provided with the following:</text>
            <para>
              <num>(1)</num>
              <text>Not less than eighty (80) square feet per dwelling unit of private usable open space directly accessible to each unit provided that no single creditable private usable open space shall be less than seventy-five (75) square feet or have a dimension of at least six (6) feet in each direction, or</text>
            </para>
            <para>
              <num>(2)</num>
              <text>150 percent of the private usable open space requirement in common usable open spaces provided that no creditable common usable open space shall be less than 300 square feet with a dimension not less than fifteen (15) feet in each direction, or</text>
            </para>
            <para>
              <num>(3)</num>
              <text>A proportional combination of both of the above. (Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
            </para>
          </para>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.064</num>
          <heading>DWELLING STANDARDS.</heading>
          <text>Section 27.22.110 in the R3 district shall apply. (Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
      </container>
      <container>
        <prefix>ARTICLE</prefix>
        <num>III</num>
        <heading>R6-D DISTRICT—MULTIPLE-FAMILY DWELLINGS (HIGH DENSITY)</heading>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.070</num>
          <heading>PERMITTED USES.</heading>
          <text>Use of buildings, or land in this district and buildings hereafter erected, structurally altered or enlarged shall be limited to the uses permitted in R1, R2, R3, R4, R4-D, R5 or R5-D Districts. (Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.072</num>
          <heading>SPECIAL USES.</heading>
          <text>Unless otherwise provided, any special uses permitted in R4, R4-D, R5 or R5-D Districts may be permitted subject to approval of a special use permit by the Planning Commission. (Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.074</num>
          <heading>OFF-STREET PARKING.</heading>
          <text>Off-street parking facilities shall be provided as required in Chapter 27.64 subject to the design standards in Section 27.25.030 in the R4-D District. (Ord. 1992-2 § 12, 1992; Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.076</num>
          <heading>MINIMUM DEVELOPMENT STANDARDS.</heading>
          <text>Residential development on properties zoned R6-D shall not exceed 50 units per acre regardless of parcel size. (Ord. 1992-4 § 1, 1992; Ord. 1992-2 § 13, 1992; Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.078</num>
          <heading>MAXIMUM COVERAGE OF PARCELS.</heading>
          <para>
            <num>(a)</num>
            <text>The maximum coverage of parcels (including enclosed or covered parking) shall be limited to fifty-five percent (55%) of the total parcel area.</text>
          </para>
          <para>
            <num>(b)</num>
            <text>All areas open to the sky, excluding driveways and accessways, shall be landscaped. (Ord. 1992-2 § 14, 1992; Ord. 1989-33 § 1, 1989; Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
          </para>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.080</num>
          <heading>MAXIMUM FLOOR AREA RATIO.</heading>
          <text>The maximum floor area ratio in this district is 3.0. (Ord. 1992-15 § 20, 1992; Ord. 1989-33 § 2, 1989; Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.082</num>
          <heading>YARD AREAS GENERALLY.</heading>
          <para>
            <num>(a)</num>
            <text>Buildings shall not be erected or enlarged unless required yard areas are provided and maintained in connection with such building, structure or enlargement. Required yards may be combined in various ways through a planned unit development to preserve and enhance the existing site elements (including sunlight, protection of existing heritage trees, creeks, waterways, historical or architecturally important sites, or structures, and archaeological sites). Such combinations shall be considered by the City as part of the planning application review.</text>
          </para>
          <para>
            <num>(b)</num>
            <text>For one family and two family dwellings the regulations of the R1-B district shall apply. (Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
          </para>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.084</num>
          <heading>FRONT YARDS.</heading>
          <text>A front yard of not less than twenty (20) feet shall be provided and maintained. (Ord. 1992-2 § 15, 1992; Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.086</num>
          <heading>SIDE YARDS.</heading>
          <text>A side yard of not less than fifteen (15) feet shall be provided and maintained. (Ord. 1992-2 § 16, 1992; Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.088</num>
          <heading>REAR YARDS.</heading>
          <text>A rear yard of not less than twenty-five (25) feet shall be provided and maintained. (Ord. 1992-2 § 17, 1992; Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.090</num>
          <heading>LANDSCAPING.</heading>
          <text>At least twenty-five (25) percent of the required rear yard shall be landscaped and planted as defined in Section 27.04.267 for usable open space only (exclusive of parking areas, driveways, or accessory facilities) and maintained in common. (Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.092</num>
          <heading>USABLE OPEN SPACE REQUIREMENTS.</heading>
          <para>
            <num>(a)</num>
            <text>The open space requirements of this district are in addition to any open space requirements resulting from the approval and filing of a subdivision map, any open space requirements imposed upon a planned development in accord with the general plan, or any required off street parking areas or driveways. Open space required by this section is intended to be for the use and enjoyment of the residents of the development.</text>
          </para>
          <para>
            <num>(b)</num>
            <text>Each dwelling unit shall be provided with the following:</text>
            <para>
              <num>(1)</num>
              <text>Not less than eighty (80) square feet per dwelling unit of private open space directly accessible to each unit provided that no single creditable private open space shall be less than seventy-five (75) square feet or have a dimension of less than six (6) feet in each direction, or</text>
            </para>
            <para>
              <num>(2)</num>
              <text>150 percent of the private usable open space requirement in common usable open spaces provided that no creditable common usable open space shall be less than 300 square feet with a dimension not less than fifteen (15) feet in each direction, or</text>
            </para>
            <para>
              <num>(3)</num>
              <text>A proportional combination of both of the above. (Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
            </para>
          </para>
        </section>
        <section>
          <num>27.28.094</num>
          <heading>DWELLING STANDARDS.</heading>
          <text>Section 27.22.110 in the R3 district shall apply. (Ord. 1986-14 § 1, 1986).</text>
        </section>
